  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime. While the breach of trust is significant, the partial restitution and the absence of a criminal record warrant a sentence toward the lower end of the sentencing guidelines to allow for rehabilitation and continued repayment of the remaining debt. A sentence of 6 months is proportional to the nature of the crime and the amount embezzled.",
